<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column10_cbf9e5-40"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col"><h2 class="kt-adv-heading10_79c830-48 wp-block-kadence-advancedheading kt-adv-heading-has-icon has-theme-palette1-color has-text-color" data-kb-block="kb-adv-heading10_79c830-48"><span class="kb-svg-icon-wrap kb-adv-heading-icon kb-svg-icon-fas_hand-point-right kb-adv-heading-icon-side-left"><svg viewBox="0 0 512 512"  fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"  aria-hidden="true"><path d="M512 199.652c0 23.625-20.65 43.826-44.8 43.826h-99.851c16.34 17.048 18.346 49.766-6.299 70.944 14.288 22.829 2.147 53.017-16.45 62.315C353.574 425.878 322.654 448 272 448c-2.746 0-13.276-.203-16-.195-61.971.168-76.894-31.065-123.731-38.315C120.596 407.683 112 397.599 112 385.786V214.261l.002-.001c.011-18.366 10.607-35.889 28.464-43.845 28.886-12.994 95.413-49.038 107.534-77.323 7.797-18.194 21.384-29.084 40-29.092 34.222-.014 57.752 35.098 44.119 66.908-3.583 8.359-8.312 16.67-14.153 24.918H467.2c23.45 0 44.8 20.543 44.8 43.826zM96 200v192c0 13.255-10.745 24-24 24H24c-13.255 0-24-10.745-24-24V200c0-13.255 10.745-24 24-24h48c13.255 0 24 10.745 24 24zM68 368c0-11.046-8.954-20-20-20s-20 8.954-20 20 8.954 20 20 20 20-8.954 20-20z"/></svg></span><span class="kb-adv-text-inner">FAQs</span></h2></div></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-accordion alignnone"><div class="kt-accordion-wrap kt-accordion-id10_46ecb4-f7 kt-accordion-has-16-panes kt-active-pane-0 kt-accordion-block kt-pane-header-alignment-left kt-accodion-icon-style-basic kt-accodion-icon-side-right" style="max-width:none"><div class="kt-accordion-inner-wrap" data-allow-multiple-open="false" data-start-open="0">
<div class="wp-block-kadence-pane kt-accordion-pane kt-accordion-pane-1 kt-pane10_38c21e-75"><div class="kt-accordion-header-wrap"><button class="kt-blocks-accordion-header kt-acccordion-button-label-show" type="button"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title-wrap"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title"><strong><strong><strong><strong><strong>What is TNREGINET?</strong></strong></strong></strong></strong></span></span><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-icon-trigger"></span></button></div><div class="kt-accordion-panel kt-accordion-panel-hidden"><div class="kt-accordion-panel-inner">
<p class="wp-block-paragraph"> TNREGINET is the Tamil Nadu government&#8217;s official online portal offering services like property registration, Encumbrance Certificate (EC) viewing, stamp duty payment, and other land-related documentation.</p>
</div></div></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-pane kt-accordion-pane kt-accordion-pane-2 kt-pane10_86c17f-82"><div class="kt-accordion-header-wrap"><button class="kt-blocks-accordion-header kt-acccordion-button-label-show" type="button"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title-wrap"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title"><strong><strong><strong><strong><strong>How can I check my Encumbrance Certificate (EC) online in Tamil Nadu?</strong></strong></strong></strong></strong></span></span><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-icon-trigger"></span></button></div><div class="kt-accordion-panel kt-accordion-panel-hidden"><div class="kt-accordion-panel-inner">
<p class="wp-block-paragraph"> To check your EC, visit the TNREGINET portal, go to “E-Services,” select “Encumbrance Certificate,” and input details like the zone, district, document number, and registration year.</p>
</div></div></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-pane kt-accordion-pane kt-accordion-pane-3 kt-pane10_aeb8a8-de"><div class="kt-accordion-header-wrap"><button class="kt-blocks-accordion-header kt-acccordion-button-label-show" type="button"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title-wrap"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title"><strong><strong><strong><strong><strong>Is TNREGINET accessible for all districts in Tamil Nadu?</strong></strong></strong></strong></strong></span></span><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-icon-trigger"></span></button></div><div class="kt-accordion-panel kt-accordion-panel-hidden"><div class="kt-accordion-panel-inner">
<p class="wp-block-paragraph"> Yes, TNREGINET provides services across all urban and rural districts of Tamil Nadu, covering all major zones and sub-registrar offices.</p>
</div></div></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-pane kt-accordion-pane kt-accordion-pane-4 kt-pane10_fe966c-69"><div class="kt-accordion-header-wrap"><button class="kt-blocks-accordion-header kt-acccordion-button-label-show" type="button"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title-wrap"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title"><strong><strong><strong><strong><strong>Do I need to register to view the Encumbrance Certificate (EC) on TNREGINET?</strong></strong></strong></strong></strong></span></span><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-icon-trigger"></span></button></div><div class="kt-accordion-panel kt-accordion-panel-hidden"><div class="kt-accordion-panel-inner">
<p class="wp-block-paragraph"> No, you can view the EC without registration. However, registration is required for certified copies and other advanced services.</p>
</div></div></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-pane kt-accordion-pane kt-accordion-pane-5 kt-pane10_e1d471-a0"><div class="kt-accordion-header-wrap"><button class="kt-blocks-accordion-header kt-acccordion-button-label-show" type="button"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title-wrap"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title"><strong><strong><strong><strong><strong>Can I download the Encumbrance Certificate (EC) from TNREGINET?</strong></strong></strong></strong></strong></span></span><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-icon-trigger"></span></button></div><div class="kt-accordion-panel kt-accordion-panel-hidden"><div class="kt-accordion-panel-inner">
<p class="wp-block-paragraph"> Yes, once you view your EC on TNREGINET, you can download it directly as a PDF by clicking the “Download” button.</p>
</div></div></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-pane kt-accordion-pane kt-accordion-pane-6 kt-pane10_0aa810-cc"><div class="kt-accordion-header-wrap"><button class="kt-blocks-accordion-header kt-acccordion-button-label-show" type="button"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title-wrap"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title"><strong><strong><strong><strong><strong>What other property-related services can I access on TNREGINET?</strong></strong></strong></strong></strong></span></span><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-icon-trigger"></span></button></div><div class="kt-accordion-panel kt-accordion-panel-hidden"><div class="kt-accordion-panel-inner">
<p class="wp-block-paragraph"> Apart from viewing ECs, TNREGINET offers services like property registration, marriage registration, guideline value search, Patta details, and more.</p>
</div></div></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-pane kt-accordion-pane kt-accordion-pane-7 kt-pane10_01cd18-bc"><div class="kt-accordion-header-wrap"><button class="kt-blocks-accordion-header kt-acccordion-button-label-show" type="button"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title-wrap"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title"><strong><strong><strong><strong><strong>Is TNREGINET secure for online payments?</strong></strong></strong></strong></strong></span></span><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-icon-trigger"></span></button></div><div class="kt-accordion-panel kt-accordion-panel-hidden"><div class="kt-accordion-panel-inner">
<p class="wp-block-paragraph"> Yes, all transactions on TNREGINET are encrypted and secure, allowing users to safely make payments via net banking, UPI, or credit/debit cards.</p>
</div></div></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-pane kt-accordion-pane kt-accordion-pane-8 kt-pane10_e46544-66"><div class="kt-accordion-header-wrap"><button class="kt-blocks-accordion-header kt-acccordion-button-label-show" type="button"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title-wrap"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title"><strong><strong><strong><strong><strong>Can non-residents of Tamil Nadu use TNREGINET?</strong></strong></strong></strong></strong></span></span><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-icon-trigger"></span></button></div><div class="kt-accordion-panel kt-accordion-panel-hidden"><div class="kt-accordion-panel-inner">
<p class="wp-block-paragraph"> No, the TNREGINET portal is exclusively available to Tamil Nadu residents for accessing property and registration services.</p>
</div></div></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-pane kt-accordion-pane kt-accordion-pane-9 kt-pane10_3e58d5-43"><div class="kt-accordion-header-wrap"><button class="kt-blocks-accordion-header kt-acccordion-button-label-show" type="button"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title-wrap"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title"><strong><strong><strong><strong>What information do I need to check EC online on TNREGINET?</strong></strong></strong></strong></span></span><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-icon-trigger"></span></button></div><div class="kt-accordion-panel kt-accordion-panel-hidden"><div class="kt-accordion-panel-inner">
<p class="wp-block-paragraph"> To check the EC online, you need the zone, district, sub-registrar office, document number, and the registration year.</p>
</div></div></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-pane kt-accordion-pane kt-accordion-pane-10 kt-pane10_87c707-e4"><div class="kt-accordion-header-wrap"><button class="kt-blocks-accordion-header kt-acccordion-button-label-show" type="button"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title-wrap"><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-title"><strong><strong><strong><strong>How can I apply for property registration online through TNREGINET?</strong></strong></strong></strong></span></span><span class="kt-blocks-accordion-icon-trigger"></span></button></div><div class="kt-accordion-panel kt-accordion-panel-hidden"><div class="kt-accordion-panel-inner">
<p class="wp-block-paragraph"> You can apply for property registration on TNREGINET by submitting online applications, paying stamp duty, and scheduling appointments with the respective sub-registrar offices.</p>
</div></div></div>
</div></div></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-infobox kt-info-box10_d3f63a-3a"><span class="kt-blocks-info-box-link-wrap info-box-link kt-blocks-info-box-media-align-top kt-info-halign-center"><div class="kt-blocks-info-box-media-container"><div class="kt-blocks-info-box-media kt-info-media-animate-none"><div class="kadence-info-box-icon-container kt-info-icon-animate-none"><div class="kadence-info-box-icon-inner-container"><span class="kb-svg-icon-wrap kb-svg-icon-fe_edit kt-info-svg-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"  fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"  aria-hidden="true"><path d="M20 14.66V20a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H4a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V6a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h5.34"/><polygon points="18 2 22 6 12 16 8 16 8 12 18 2"/></svg></span></div></div></div></div><div class="kt-infobox-textcontent"><h2 class="kt-blocks-info-box-title">Final Words</h2><p class="kt-blocks-info-box-text">TNREGINET is Tamil Nadu’s official online portal for property registration, Encumbrance Certificate (EC) services, guideline value checks, marriage registration, and other legal document processes. This all-in-one platform helps citizens save time, reduce paperwork, and access essential services through a secure, transparent, and user-friendly system. With online payments, document tracking, and quick access to land and registration records, TNREGINET makes property and legal documentation faster, easier, and more convenient across Tamil Nadu.</p></div></span></div>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"></p>
